workouts.title: Push Press - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: Push Press of choice (barbell or log)
4 sets of 5 @RPE6 - I just want you to keep this ticking over during this block, so we'll keep the intensity climbing for the next 10 weeks, but starting out nice and light here

workouts.title: Strict Press - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 10 @RPE6 - Just to get an idea of a conservative weight for this first week, as next week and the week after we will push the 10s quite hard, so whatever you think you should go for, you could probably go 5-10kg lighter

workouts.title: BTN Seated Press - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: Work up to a top set of 10, nice and light, then drop weight for a more pump focused set of 15, weekly we'll be pushing the numbers up here

workouts.title: Single Arm Cable Lat Raise - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 2 sets working to absolute failure, start with your weaker side, then match reps with stronger side. Start in a full ROM and as you begin to fatigue, you can reduce ROM until you are pulsing reps at the bottom:
First set in the 8-12 rep range with 3-6 more reps pulsing
Second set in the 12-15 rep range (lighter) with 3-6 more reps pulsing

workouts.title: DB Rear Delt/Tricep Rope Extension - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 1) DB Rear Delt Raises - 3 sets of 15 - Light and pump focused
2) Rope Tricep Extension - 3 sets of 15 - Light and pump focused
2mins rest between sets, no rest between exercises

workouts.title: Knee Extension/Squat W/ Reach - Hypertrohpy - Week 1
notes: - 2 set of 20 - Light and pump focused
- 2 sets of 10-12 - Fullest ROM possible that feels safe and pain free
2mins rest between sets, no rest between exercises

workouts.title: Deadlift - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 6 sets of 4 @RPE6 - You can adjust weight up and down throughout the sets where needed if you feel it's getting too heavy/light, but form and speed need to be spot on.

workouts.title: Snatch Grip Back Extension - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 20 reps - For this first week I want you to literally just work with the bar, we'll load this more as the weeks go on, but 20 reps should still suck anyway

workouts.title: Behind The Back Hold - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 75s - Super light here, be conservative in your weight selection so there's room to put more weight on for same time next week

workouts.title: Bent Over Row - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 12 - Light and easy, just work in a full ROM with good hinge mechanics - 2mins rest

workouts.title: Close Grip Pulldown - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 2 sets of 15-20 - Load heavier from set 1 to set 2, full supination, big lat and bicep pump

workouts.title: EZ Bar Curl - Hypertrohpy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 15-20 - Ascend weight each set and end on the lower end of the rep range, with a massive pump here

workouts.title: Strongman Engine - Hypertrophy - Week 1
workouts.reps: 2k Row or Ski-Erg - First week on this, find a baseline for this movement, and we will aim to improve that time quite dramatically over the next 5 weeks

workouts.title: Bench Press - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 5 sets of 5 @RPE6.5 - Just get everything moving and feeling good here, make sure the positions are pain free and you have good thoracic extension. No need to worry about loading the bar much today

workouts.title: Back Squat - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 12 @RPE6.5 - Just get a feel for these higher rep squats, the reps will be falling off every couple of weeks, so just get a pump today and hit good depth

workouts.title: Leg Press - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 1 top set of 6 @RPE6.5 - Keep this light, but over the weeks, this should become really heavy and hard
2 drop sets of 15 @RPE6.5 - Light and more pump focused on these, just try to flow through these reps a little more

workouts.title: Straight bar Pushdown/ EZ Bar Skullcrusher - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: - 3 sets of 12 @heavier, but weight should be limited by the prefatigue

workouts.title: KB Tib Raise/Machine Calf Raise - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: - Light kb for today for 20 reps - progress load weekly

workouts.title: Romanian Deadlift - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 2 sets of 20 @RPE6.5 - Keep this super light and just work in a full ROM with good tempo control, next week we punch things up, so keep plenty in the tank

workouts.title: Farmers Walk - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 4 sets of 10m drop turn 10m in sub 13s - We want to be moving fast and well here, focus on your pick-ups and drop turns, the time cap should dictate weight selection for today

workouts.title: Sandbag Front Carry - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 60m - nasal breathing front carry here with a light sandbag on week 1

workouts.title: Neutral Grip Pull Up - Hypertrophy - Week 1
workouts.reps: Neutral Grip Chin-Ups
notes: 10min EDT - In a 10min time cap, perform as many reps as possible, resting where needed, and keeping reps in the tank on every cluster, so that you can get more out of the 10min cap

workouts.title: Cable Curl - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 1 set of 20 - 1 set of 15 - 1 set of 10 - Ascend load every set and end heavy, should be getting a big pump here

workouts.title: Incline DB Curl - Hypertrophy - Week 1
notes: 3 sets of 15 - Working in a lengthened range here, so we can keep this light for today, just make sure to get a really full ROM

workouts.title: Strongman Engine - Hypertrophy - Week 1 - Session 4
workouts.reps: 30mins of Steady State Cardio on machine of choice - I'm happy for you to do this here, or on a rest day, whatever works best, but we're looking to work in RPE6 area to just get a sweat, should feel restorative every week
